Package com.example.trojanplanner.model

Class Entrant

java.lang.Object
com.example.trojanplanner.model.User
com.example.trojanplanner.model.Entrant
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Entrant extends User
Entrant class that is extended from User class that stores information relating to events. An Entrant is tied in and tracks a participant's behavior while engaging in eventbuddy's events.

    • replaceEventMatchingId

      public boolean replaceEventMatchingId(Event event)
      Replaces an event object from any of the event arrays with the new event object if the event ids match. Only replaces one instance under the assumption that no duplicates should ever appear.
      Parameters:
      event - The new event object to replace if ids match
      Returns:
      true if a replace happened, false if not

    • returnOrganizer

      public Organizer returnOrganizer()
      Returns the same user as an Organizer class.
      Allows converting an entrant into an organizer even if they aren't one yet; this allows a regular entrant to become an organizer like in FacilitySetupFragment.
      Returns:
      The equivalent organizer class for this entrant
